
[1]irruption

   IRRUP'TION, n. [L. irruption; in and rumpo, to break or burst.]

   1. A bursting in; a breaking or sudden violent rushing into a place.
   Holland has been often inundated by irruptions of the sea.

   2. A sudden invasion or incursion; a sudden, violent inroad, or
   entrance of invaders into a place or country; as the irruption of the
   northern nations into France and Italy.
